In 1972, Arthur C. Clarke wrote the short story &quot;A Meeting with Medusa&quot; which featured nuclear ramjet operating on Jupiter.<br>
<br>
<br>
The US had a large program running from the late '50s to early '60s, to build a nuclear ramjet cruise missile, the SLAM. The codename was &quot;Project Pluto&quot;<br>
<br>
Engine/reactors were built and successfully tested.<br>
